name: PLA (Standard FDM Filament)
description: Polylactic acid standard FDM 3D printing filament target. Biodegradable thermoplastic with good stiffness and detail.

name: PETG (Durable Engineering Filament)
description: Polyethylene terephthalate glycol-modified engineering filament. Excellent chemical resistance and durability.

name: Polymaker PolySmooth (PVB-Based)
description: PVB-based filament with smooth surface finish, alcohol-smoothable. Targets aesthetic and post-processable prints.

name: Polyvinyl Butyral (PVB)
description: PVB filament with good interlayer adhesion and alcohol solubility for smoothing.

name: Machinable Wax (Print2Cast)
description: Wax-based filament designed for lost-wax casting workflows. Low melting point, clean burnout.

name: Silk PLA (Glossy Aesthetic Filament)
description: Modified PLA with silk-like glossy surface finish for aesthetic prints.

name: High-Resolution Resin (50um Voxel Target)
description: UV-curable resin targeting 50 micron voxel resolution. High hardness and layer adhesion.

name: Minimum Viable Wax Filament
description: Optimization target for the minimum viable safe wax filament. Defines acceptable ranges for key properties with priority weights.
